---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: "The Sectors"
description: "The fifteen essential-cost sectors Uncost tracks, in fixed order — from Food to Leisure."
---
{% from "partials/content-needed.njk" import block as gap %}
<section class="blk blk--first">
  <p class="eyebrow">The Sectors</p>
  <h1 class="sec">Fifteen sectors of essential cost.</h1>
  <p class="lead">The essentials of a life, grouped into fifteen sectors in a fixed order. Each has a dossier: what it covers, where automation could reduce cost, the guardrail, and the honest evidence status.</p>
  {{ gap("sectors-index-intro", "the export's framing paragraph for the hub is design-authored; author from the July source once approved") }}
</section>
<section class="blk blk--cream2">
  <div class="card-grid">
{%- for sector in catalog.sectors %}
    <a class="sec-card" href="/sectors/{{ sector.slug }}/"><span class="sec-card-num">{{ sector.num }} / 15</span><span class="sec-card-name">{{ sector.name }}</span><span class="status status--{{ sector.statusClass }}">{{ sector.status }}</span></a>
{%- endfor %}
  </div>
</section>
